    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The three dispatch strategies &mdash; explicit conditional, dispatch table, message passing &mdash; correspond directly to patterns in mainstream OOP. Explicit conditionals are <code>isinstance</code> checks. Dispatch tables are the visitor pattern. Message passing is virtual method dispatch. Python classes combine all three: <code>isinstance</code> for ad-hoc checks, <code>__init_subclass__</code> for registry patterns, and regular methods for message passing.</p>
    <p class="mt-2">SICP's insight is that these are <em>all</em> the same mechanism (dispatch on type) organized differently. Data-directed programming is the most extensible: new types and new operations can be added independently. This is exactly the expression problem that haunts every language design.</p>

